%N A396129 Consider the square spiral with its cells numbered starting at 0. Six players take turns and place knights at the smallest unoccupied cell not attacked by an existing knight of a different player. Sequence lists squares occupied by the first player.
%C A396129 A variant of A392177 with four players.
%H A396129 Rémy Sigrist, <a href="/A396129/b396129.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000</a>
%H A396129 Brady Haran, Jonas Karlsson, and N. J. A. Sloane, <a href="https://youtu.be/UiX4CFIiegM">Red & Black Knights (extraordinary result)</a>; <a href="https://youtu.be/VgmDuBCayPw">Amazing Chessboard Patterns (extra)</a>, YouTube Numberphile videos, May 2026.
%H A396129 Scott R. Shannon, <a href="/A396129/a396129.png">Six knights after 2500000 knights have been placed.</a>
%H A396129 Rémy Sigrist, <a href="/A396129/a396129.gp.txt">PARI program</a>
